{"word":"ἄνασσα","slug":"ἄνασσα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄνασσα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <a href='S:ἄναξ'><el>ἄναξ</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a queen, lady, mistress</i>, addressed to goddesses, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; also to a mortal, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>generally, like <el>ἄναξ</el> IV, <el>ἄνασσα ὀργίων</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}